This paper deals with object detection in autonomous driving scenarios, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a generative model to estimate bounding box label uncertainties, which involves probabilistic modeling and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL) that deal with similar topics.
